snippet.textDisplay: I would call Piyush Mishra, The Tony Bennett of Indian music. He takes you on an unassuming journey with his songs, so much so that you don't want to return to your own real world, once you enter the world he makes you experience with his songs. If not for the internet and YouTube, this artist would been buried like many others before him, in the sand of indian music industry-hippocrates and remix song peddlers.
